Eureka Hunter Pipeline, LLC also considered the impact of a more likely release.  This alternative release is characterized as an accident during a daily routine.  Using air modeling software, the impact distance of a potential explosion of the vapor cloud formed after this release was calculated to be 0.32 miles.  A limited number of off-site receptors, such as residences, roads and staging areas are located within this radius.  Eureka Hunter Pipeline, LLC has implemented safety precautions and procedures designed to prevent and mitigate catastrophic releases.  The Carbide Facility has active operating, maintenance, training, and inspection procedures.  Eureka Hunter Pipeline, LLC provides annual emergency response training to its employees. In addition, Eureka Hunter Pipeline, LLC coordinates with local emergency responders including the Local Emergency Planning Committee.



Eureka Hunter Pipeline, LLC is committed to the following:

- Preventing accidents;

- Training our employees in correct response procedures in the event of an accident;

- Participating in community emergency preparedness;

- Addressing any citizen concerns by fully explaining potential hazards associated with the Carbide Facility operations and all steps being taken to prevent and mitigate accidents.

With these objectives in mind, this Risk Management Plan has been developed to provide information about our management of the risks associated with the liquids removal and compression process.  



